10/02/2005
ANKARA, Turkey -- Two senior energy officials in Turkey have been detained because of suspected corruption, Energy Minister Hilmi Guler confirmed on Wednesday (9 February). He was speaking at a news conference about the pace of a major investigation into alleged embezzlement and corruption in the energy sector. Guler said the two officials are managers of the state-run companies for power generation and natural gas distribution, and he did not rule out more detentions or dismissals following the probe. (NTV - 10/02/05)
